|MKB                       @}--- Finesse ---{@                 |XX0

Finesse is a measure of a Swashbuckler's combative abilities. As
a Swashbuckler becomes more skilled, they will learn to fight with
more finesse. Different fighting styles will require more or less
finesse depending on their difficulty. More about these finesse
requirements can be found in sbhelp '|YKBstyles|XX0'.

A Swashbuckler starts with 1 point of finesse and gains one 
additional point of finesse per guild level. They can then run up
to or equal to that finesse in different styles. Here are some
examples:

    Bodach is a guild level 9 Swashbuckler. He could run:
        '|YKBcstrike|XX0', '|YKBcalledshot|XX0' and '|YKBslash|XX0'             OR
        '|YKBriposte|XX0', '|YKBcalledshot|XX0', '|YKBospin|XX0' and '|YKBparry|XX0'    OR
        '|YKBriposte|XX0', '|YKBospin|XX0', '|YKBsdodge|XX0', and '|YKBslash|XX0'       ...

    Cowman is a guild level 15 Swashbuckler. He could run:
        '|YKBsdance|XX0', and '|YKBimpale|XX0'                          OR
        '|YKBtblades|XX0', '|YKBflourish|XX0' and '|YKBflurry|XX0'              OR
        '|YKBsdance|XX0', '|YKBsdodge|XX0', and '|YKBparry|XX0'                 ...

